  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AboutGameplayController
    This class handles the about screen during gameplay
    Assets
    This class is used to cache assets and control reading image files.
    CardController
    This class is a display of a single card.
    CustomAlerts
    This class is a place to store common popup dialogs and display them in the program
    GameScreenController
    Use to control the GameScreen scene.
    GameSetupController
    This class is used to control the GameSetup scene.
    HowToPlayController
    This class is used to display instructions on how to play the game.
    JukeBoxController
    This class handles the Jukebox Scene

    This class handles the about screen for the level editor
    LEActionTilesController
    This class is used to control the action tiles page of the level editor guide.
    LeaderboardController
    Controller for the leaderboard window
    LECanvas
    LECanvas class is used to interact with the canvas(also reffered as render) on the Level Editor view.
    LEChangeColorController
    This class is used to control the change color window.
    LEColorController
    This class is used to control the change color page of the level editor guide.
    LEHowToPlayController
    This class is used to control the Level editor guide.
    LEMainController
    This is the class responsible for managing the main view of the Level Editor as well as all the class interactions needed to make it work
    LENewController
    Class that manages the Create New Level screen
    LEStartController
    This class manages the start screen of the level editor
    LEStartingPositionsController
    This class is used to control the starting positions page of the level editor guide.
    LETilesController
    This class is used to control the tiles page of the level editor guide.
    LoadGameController
    Screen to load a previously saved game.
    Main
    FrontEnd.Main class for this app, starts the window and opens up the 'Start' window
    MenuScreenController
    Use to control the Menu screen scene.
    PickPlayerController
    After game setup, show numbers of choiceBox to let players select a player profile for different players, set these files to an ArrayList for gameBoard to use and run.
    ProfilesController
    A controller class for profiles.fxml which allows a user to show the player profiles saved, create new player profiles, delete player profiles and view player profiles.
    ResizableCanvas
    This is a small class that allows for the Canvas to be bound to the size of the screen Some of this is code from StackOverflow, some of it is all me
    Slot
    This is what we store our tiles in for use in the level editor
    StartScreenController
    Controller for the "Press any button screen" lets you open the main menu screen.
    StateLoad
    Interface to set up each window when switching between scenes.
    WindowLoader
    This class is used to load new windows.
    WinScreenController
    Screen that shows once someone has won the game.
